HEADWORD: Trappous
<hw>Trap"pous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Trap</er>
a kind of rock.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Of or performance to trap;
resembling trap, or partaking of its form or qualities;
trappy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

